1
00:00:00,100 --> 00:00:02,896
Real work already has context behind it.

2
00:00:02,846 --> 00:00:11,269
It may live in calendars, messages, emails, documents, dashboards, spreadsheets, trackers, decks, or discussion history.

3
00:00:11,269 --> 00:00:15,528
The task brief should point to the materials that can actually change the result.

4
00:00:15,528 --> 00:00:17,413
Do not paste everything.

5
00:00:17,413 --> 00:00:19,067
Build a source map.

6
00:00:19,067 --> 00:00:27,480
For each source, state what it contains, why it matters, how current it is, and whether it is authoritative, supporting, or only background.

7
00:00:27,480 --> 00:00:29,750
Put primary inputs first.

8
00:00:29,750 --> 00:00:32,500
A signed requirement beats a chat summary.

9
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,759
A current dashboard beats last quarter's screenshot.

10
00:00:35,759 --> 00:00:40,346
A repository file beats a copied snippet when implementation details matter.

11
00:00:40,346 --> 00:00:44,173
The agent should know which source wins when two items disagree.

12
00:00:44,173 --> 00:00:46,846
Label uncertainty instead of hiding it.

13
00:00:46,846 --> 00:00:52,923
Mark assumptions, missing records, stale numbers, and facts that still require confirmation.

14
00:00:52,923 --> 00:00:58,971
This lets the first version separate evidence from inference rather than smoothing both into one confident story.

15
00:00:58,971 --> 00:01:08,163
For a weekly operating brief, the source package might include the current project tracker, meeting decisions, incident notes, and the calendar for upcoming deadlines.

16
00:01:08,163 --> 00:01:11,961
It does not need every historical message the team has ever sent.

17
00:01:11,961 --> 00:01:14,653
The common failure is context dumping.

18
00:01:14,653 --> 00:01:20,221
A long attachment list can bury the signal, create contradictions, and waste review time.

19
00:01:20,221 --> 00:01:25,942
Include a source only when it informs a claim, a constraint, a decision, or a required output.

20
00:01:25,942 --> 00:01:29,682
First, provide the materials that can change the artifact.

21
00:01:29,682 --> 00:01:33,759
Second, identify which sources are current and authoritative.

22
00:01:33,759 --> 00:01:38,397
Third, label missing facts and uncertainty instead of letting the agent guess.
